    },
    {
      "type": "column",
      "text": "Brief in the case of Rose Chambers, Widow of Aaron Chambers, Private Co G, 118th Regt. U.S.C. Troops. resident of Henderson County and State of Ky. Post Office address: Henderson, Ky.",
      "bbox": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 30,
        "width": 100,
        "height": 10
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "column",
      "text": "DECLARATION AND IDENTIFICATION IN DUE FORM. PROOF EXHIBITED.",
      "bbox": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 40,
        "width": 100,
        "height": 10
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "column",
      "text": "Service. The soldier was enrolled Sept. 19, 1864, and is reported by the Adjutant General. \"Died November 6, 1864, of disease in field Hospital Va.\"",
      "bbox": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 50,
        "width": 100,
        "height": 10
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "column",
      "text": "Death. Testimony of the 1st Sergeant of same Co. and Regt that the soldier died date as above of Diarrhea contracted in the service, and that he was a man of sound physical body when he entered the Army, a good soldier and of steady and sober habits. Two other persons testify to his sound condition at enrollment. Affidavit of Claimant that the officers of the Regt being northern men she is unable to procure a commissioned officer certificate etc.",
      "bbox": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 60,
        "width": 100,
        "height": 10
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "column",
      "text": "Marriage. Proof of Cohabitation since 1837 and recognition as man and wife by the community since that time and up to the time when he enlisted. No legal marriage the State law requiring none for persons of Color.",
      "bbox": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 70,
        "width": 100,
        "height": 10
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "column",
      "text": "Names and dates of birth of children. None under 16 years now living.",
      "bbox": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 80,
        "width": 100,
        "height": 10
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "column",
      "text": "Loyalty. Shown",
      "bbox": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 90,
        "width": 100,
        "height": 10
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "column",
      "text": "Agent and his P.O. address. None address Claimant Henderson, Ky.",
      "bbox": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 100,
        "width": 100,
        "height": 10
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "column",
      "text": "Admitted December 13, 1867, to a Pension of $ Eight per month, commencing November 7, 1864. P.H. Berkaw, Examining Clerk.",
      "bbox": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 110,
        "width": 100,
        "height": 10
      }
    },
